::DarkMouse::
She looked at him for a moment.
"I see. As you command, my commander."
She climbed up and started up the lazar and started drilling.
Within minutes, 100 feet of the new tunnel had been cleared away and she 
stopped the drill to inspect the work.  She got back on the drill and aimed 
the lazar at a slight upward angel and drilled heading to the surface.
"Hopefully in a few hours commander, we should reach the surface.  We could 
have this tunnel completed by nightfall if luck be with us."
She turned and looked at Quickstrike.  She started to think that maybe he 
wasn't as bad as she origianlly thought.  She them remembered how he had two 
other bots after him and decided that he was out of reach. Besides, she 
thought, he hated her.
"Commander, don't let me keep you from your other duties.  I appreciate the 
time you took with me here, I don't want to keep you from more important 
matters. Your an important leader, I'm sure there are other things you'd 
rather do than waste yout precious time with me."

She looked down at the controls trying not to look at Quickstrike.

----------------Original Message--------
From: Talon Harvilicz  <wilddance_mare@h...>

Subject: Neo Beast Wars



Quickstrike:


Quickstrike tilted his head and pondered how he was going to do this. He
wasn't the right bot to do this job, with the handi-cap on his hands. They
weren't built for this operation.

He turned his head to Dark Mouse, not sure how to explain. He held his
mismatched hands out, showing her both the arm that ended with the wide
hooded cobra and the other with eight exremely long fingers.

"Maybe you should work th' angles, eh?" he said, drawing back his arms. The
strips of metal at his cheeks quivered lightly.
